===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

Unclear. Possibly a {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} of a man with the neck in shackles — original form of {{och-l|鞅|tr=*ʔaŋʔ}}.<ref>張世超、孫凌安、金国泰、馬如森 『金文形義通解』 中文出版社、1996年、1358-1359頁。
季旭昇撰 『説文新証』 芸文印書館、2014年、451-452頁。
林志強等評注 『《文源》評注』 中国社会科学出版社、2017年、232-233頁。</ref> Later borrowed to represent {{och-l|央|center}} as an instance of {{liushu|j|nocap=y}}.

''{{w|Shuowen}}'' interprets it as a person inside a house.

===Etymology===
{{och-l|於|tr=ʔa}} plus terminative suffix *''-ŋ'', hence literally "to get to be in the middle" ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). See {{och-l|於|tr=ʔa}} for further etymology.

